    "summary": "My motivation to connect people and nature comes from the beauty and wonders I can see in the living environment around us. Nature's complexity, resilience, forces, gifts and so much more, speaks to us in many ways. The fact remains that nature is the foundation of our society and wellbeing. This perception encourages me to keep contributing to creating an environment where society and nature can thrive.  \n\nI consider myself as a creative and critical thinker, which helps me get to the core of problems to resolve them. My broad background in sustainability, business economics and international development allows me to analyze, break down and simplify complex challenges. My special interests go to biodiversity conservation, climate change adaptation & mitigation, sustainable land management and sustainable agriculture. I am a strong communicator and connector, and I enjoy being with people that can challenge or inspire me. \n\nI am thankful for the professional experiences I've gained, making me a capable professional in the field of environmental challenges. I have experience in doing project management, research & impact assessments, facilitating dialogues, strategic thinking and consultative services, and operating in a dynamic, international context; liaising with stakeholders such as civil society organizations, governments, businesses. Without too much effort, I can switch roles and 'languages', to communicate and work efficiently with various parties.\n\nI continue to develop myself by keep looking for challenges, be it volunteering at local sustainable initiatives, or literally getting my hands dirty in learning agroforestry and doing conservation. I am confident in my ability to bundle all these experiences and, utilize them effectively.",
